Attention Zane Trace Community and Ross county:

The Zane Trace Local School District has received several reports that a gentleman is circulating in Ross county soliciting on behalf of Zane Trace employees or the school district as a fundraising opportunity. We want to inform people that this is fictitious in nature and that they are not affiliated with the school district. If you are approached by a gentleman going door to door on behalf of Zane Trace Local Schools, please contact the Ross County Sheriff's Department and notify the school. Thank you!

Mr. Jerry Mowery
Superintendent
Zane Trace Local Schools

Message from Superintendent Jerry Mowery:

Welcome back to the 2020-2021 school year! We are delighted to have our staff and students returning for another challenging year. As you have probably heard from our faculty, we missed our students and we are excited to see all of our ZT kids back in our brick and mortar setting once again. The ways we provide a quality education have changed from the delivery of instruction, the way we transport, the way we feed our children, and the types of services we can provide. The Zane Trace School District is committed to doing everything we can with the resources available to keep students and staff safe! It is imperative we work together in… More

post_text:
2020-2021 5th-12th Grade ZT Students and Parents!

We are working on Middle School and High School schedules for next school year and we wanted to make sure everyone has the opportunity to sign up for band!

We usually go over this information with the 4th grade in the spring, but we had to get a little creative this year so we made a video with the information that we usually discuss.

We have a lot of talent at Zane Trace and there are usually several students in each grade that are curious about band or don't know about our program so I wanted to make sure to get the information out to everyone else as well. It's never too late to get started!

Please take some time to review our Zane Trace Band 5th-12th Grade Band Program Youtube Video and the appropriate Band Sign Up Information Letter.

If you would like to sign up, just fill out the appropriate Google Form and Submit it back to us at your earliest convenience.

https://www.zanetrace.org/Band-Department.html

RED FOR ED RALLY:

In response to the recent confirmation of coronavirus cases in Ohio, and Governor DeWine’s declaration of a public health emergency, we are adjusting our plans for the Rally for Public Schools on March 18.

We will not be holding an in-person rally at the statehouse. Instead, we will be holding a “virtual rally” at 3:30 pm on March 18 to kick off two weeks of action in support of the students in our public schools. This tele-conference will display the breadth of our public schools coalition, update attendees on the voucher crisis in our school districts, and engage activists in concrete next steps to protect public education.

Please RSVP below if you can join us in our virtual rally on March 18th!

We need to organize mass support for the vouchers policy changes in the House version of Senate Bill 89 before April 1st. If that deadline passes without legislative action, over 1200 schools around the state will qualify for EdChoice vouchers.

https://actionnetwork.org/events/virtual-rally-for-public-schools/

Red for Ed Rally - Wednesday, March 18, 2020

Currently, Ohio law sponsors an EdChoice Scholarship Program that uses taxpayer funds to pay for educational vouchers for students to attend private schools as an alternative choice to public schools that have been labeled "underperforming" by the Ohio state report card system.

This is a blatant misuse of local tax dollars as communities have no say in this program, but are Forced to pay the tab! Furthermore, the private schools DO NOT have any accountability system or state card rating that qualifies them to be rated as a better choice than the local public school that has made the list for under performance.

We need community support at the Red…

Furthermore, the private schools DO NOT have any accountability system or state card rating that qualifies them to be rated as a better choice than the local public school that has made the list for under performance.

We need community support at the Red…

Join us for a fun, family-friendly Donkey Basketball game this Saturday, February 22nd in the Zane Trace Middle School Gymnasium at 3:30pm. Tickets are only $6 in advance, $8 at the door, and FREE for kids 5 and under. Tickets can be purchased in the Middle School Office, High School Office, or online at vancoevents.com/BDB.

Concessions (featuring CHICK-FIL-A sandwiches) will be available. There will also be free donkey rides for kids 12 and under if accompanied by a parent/guardian.

Proceeds benefit the Zane Trace Band program to purchase music, equipment, and trailer repairs.

Anyone 16 and older can play in the game for free. Email zanetraceband@gmail.com to sign-up!

We look forward to seeing everyone on Saturday!
"How 'Bout That Band?!"

post_text:
The Southeast District Athletic Board has gone to all online sales for boys’ and girls’ basketball presale tickets at the sectional and district tournaments. The Board reduced the price of the presale ticket by $1.00 to help offset the fees associated with online ticket purchasing. Tickets purchased at the gate will remain $5.00 for sectional and $6.00 for district tournament games.

The link to purchase online tickets is https://ohsaa.org/tickets.

Purchasers may choose the game they wish to attend and designate their support. Upon the conclusion of the game, the purchasers of tickets for the winning team will automatically receive an email with details to purchase tickets for the next game.

While we recognize this is a new process and there may be fans who have difficulty purchasing online tickets, we have heard many different strategies being considered by schools to assist those with difficulties.

post_text:
College Credit Plus: Pickaway Ross Parent Meeting

Are you a current sophomore planning on attending Pickaway-Ross in the 2020-21 school year and would like to take college classes?

Find out how at our Parent Informational Meeting!

When: January 21, 2020, (Tuesday) 6:00 PM
Location: Pickaway-Ross Career & Technology Center (Commons/Cafeteria)
Who: Parents/Guardians/Students

- Did you know you can take College Credit Plus courses at PRCTC without ever leaving the main campus?
- Four PRCTC teachers act as adjunct professors through Hocking College or Shawnee State University.
- Credits earned are guaranteed to transfer to any other public college in Ohio
- Students earn high school credit and college credit at the same time.
- The courses are free!
- The table below lists the current CCP courses we offer at PRCTC.

More information: https://www.zanetrace.org/pdf/College-Credit-Plus-Parent-Informational-Meeting-at-PRCTC.pdf

Dear Parents or Guardian:

Zane Trace High School, in collaboration with Nationwide Children's Hospital, is providing a training for the 11th grade called Signs of Suicide. The Sign of Suicide Prevention Program (SOS) is a school-based suicide prevention program supported by SAMHSA. The Goal of the curriculum is to prevent and reduce suicidal behavior by expanding the safety net for students experiencing mental and emotional distress. The training uses a video to help guide classroom discussions.

Students are trained to recognize warning signs of suicide in a friend as well as an appropriate response. Additionally, students are provided the opportunity to speak to a school counselor if they…
